        "content": "<p>Thanks for the replies everyone.</p>\n<p>I'm focusing on Ruben's reply as the tactics are within the small beginner set.</p>\n<p>Can I then ask, does the final <code>linearity</code> confirm <code>False</code> in the same way <code>numbers at h</code> does in MoP where <code>h</code> is a numerically false proposition?</p>\n<p>And back to vanilla lean, would <code>num_norm</code> do the same? I tried and couldn't find a way to prove False for <code>h:2=3</code>.</p>\n<hr>\n<p>update - <code>linearith</code> works:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Tactic</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">¬</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"mi\">4</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">intro</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ht</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">linarith</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
